snippet.textDisplay:
Full disclosure, im only half way through cause i felt the need to help at this point. It may turn out fine, you might have to redo it. I will finish watching, BUT FIRST.

Yeast feeds on sugar.
Salt murders yeast.

That being said:
In a mixing bowl have

3 cups flour
Pinch of salt
Mix slightly
Make a well in the middle.

Have your 1 cup of warm water (i personally aim for 115F... But im in northern IL might be different for others.) In a measuring cup.

Dissolve 2TBSP sugar in water
I use 2 1/4tsp (should be 1 packet. But i have a jar) yeast with sugar water cause why not have a weird measurement. It will get frothy.

Once you see its foamy, put 2TBSP oil in the middle of the flours well. Then add the water mixture to the well and start mixing with a fork... Or whatever you want.


From there i end up taking it out of the bowl and kneading until well combined. Oil the bowl, place back. Cover it so no air touches it. Let it double in size.

Once its risen, punch it back and man handle all you want.

From here, either place in bread pans or just free bake it. But from this moment on, dont touch it. Let it raise again.

Bake it.


Also, since i haven't continued the video yet, idk your baking method.

But i just found like 3 days ago that a pan of hot water (just to make it steamy as you did) in the oven as it bakes WILL help the texture of the bread. Its crazy to learn.

Now I shall continue the video.


(Finished it)
Congrats on the bread working out. :)
